COVID-19 Status 💉 🦠

As of 7:13AM PT today, over 1.5 million Canadians have tested positive for COVID-19. Sadly, 26.7 thousand have died.

In the last day, 936 new infections were reported and 4 deaths. This is trending upwards.

Fortunately, 51.2 million doses of the vaccine have been administered. For those 12 years and older, 82.1% have their 1st shot and 71.7% are fully vaccinated!

Vaccination is slowing down, but there are 11.5 million doses in the freezer. It currently takes ~72 days for new deliveries to get into arms.

At the current rate, Canadians should achieve herd immunity around Dec-14 when 80% of the entire population is fully vaccinated. There is no approved vaccine for children aged 11 or younger.
